OL,3,CRemembering Britain's first Black
OL,4,Cpoliceman
OL,6,FCarlisle's MP is supporting a campaign
OL,7,Fto have Britain's first black
OL,8,Fpoliceman honoured in the National
OL,9,FPortrait Gallery.
OL,11,FWatch Kieran Macfadzean's report:
OL,13,FJohn Kent joined Carlisle City Police
OL,14,Fas a constable on 1837, having first
OL,15,Fserved in Maryport as a watchman.
OL,17,FHe was the son of Thomas Kent, an
OL,18,Fworker enslaved by the Senhouse
OL,19,FFamily, who eventually gave him his
OL,20,Ffreedom.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/6
