OL,3,CRemembering Britain's first Black
OL,4,Cpoliceman
OL,6,FThis week marks 140 years since John
OL,7,FKent's death.
OL,9,FIn 2025, pupils at Grayrigg primary
OL,10,Fschool began a class project
OL,11,Fresearching his life eventually
OL,12,Fpresenting their findings to a group
OL,13,Fof stakeholders in Carlisle.
OL,15,FNow, a fully fledged campaign is
OL,16,Funderway to commemorate his life with
OL,17,Fan Historic England blue plaque, as
OL,18,Fwell as a portrait in Carlisle's
OL,19,Frailway station where he worked at the
OL,20,Fend of his policing career.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1784733509
OL,3,CRemembering Britain's first Black
OL,4,Cpoliceman
OL,6,FSome pupils read the book Britain's
OL,7,FFirst Black Policeman by former
OL,8,FCumbrian police officer Ray Greenhow,
OL,9,Fwho has backed the campaign.
OL,11,FMr Greenhow said: "John braved a
OL,12,Fnumber of incidents, including being
OL,13,Fthreatened with a blunderbuss and he'd
OL,14,Fbeen threatened a couple of times with
OL,15,Fwith knives. Yet he continued to do
OL,16,Fhis job, which was basically
OL,17,Fprotecting the community."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1784733509
OL,3,CRemembering Britain's first Black
OL,4,Cpoliceman
OL,6,FProject lead Niall McNulty told ITV
OL,7,FBorder: "The pupils each took turns in
OL,8,Ftelling us a bit about John's life and
OL,9,Fthe passion they had to tell that
OL,10,Fstory kind of rubs off on you. So a
OL,11,Ffew of us thought, 'We need to do
OL,12,Fsomething about this.' We invited
OL,13,Fother people along and it started to
OL,14,Fsnowball."
OL,16,FJohn Kent is buried in an unmarked
OL,17,Fgrave in Carlisle. An ongoing
OL,18,Ffundraiser aims to have a headstone
OL,19,Finstalled to denote his final resting
OL,20,Fplace.
OL,26,@oD@IOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
